# PostgreSQL Setup Instructions:
#
# Windows:
# 1. Download PostgreSQL from: https://www.postgresql.org/download/windows/
# 2. Install with default settings (port 5432)
# 3. Use pgAdmin GUI or command line to create database and user
# 4. Update DATABASE_URL above with your credentials
#
# Linux/Unix:
# 1. Install PostgreSQL: sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-contrib
# 2. Create database: sudo -u postgres psql -c "CREATE DATABASE ar_interior_db;"
# 3. Create user: sudo -u postgres psql -c "CREATE USER your_user WITH PASSWORD 'your_password';"
# 4. Grant privileges: sudo -u postgres psql -c "GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE ar_interior_db TO your_user;"
# 5. Update DATABASE_URL above with your credentials
